Preparation
• Stretch your arms, legs, hips, and back before starting.
• Find a flat, open area with enough space to move comfortably.
• Ensure you're wearing proper footwear to avoid slipping.
• After pressing START, there’s a 4-second countdown before the challenge begins.
During the Challenge
• Begin by getting on all fours with your hands directly under your shoulders and your knees under your hips.
• Keep your back flat and engage your core for stability.
• Start crawling forward by moving your right hand and left foot at the same time, followed by the left hand and right foot.
• Maintain a steady rhythm throughout the exercise.
• Keep your knees close to the ground (about 1-2 inches off the floor) and your movements controlled.
• If the time runs out, you'll be automatically back to the homepage.
Finishing the Challenge
• When done, enter the number of rotations you completed in the ROT field, then press DONE.
Exercise Guide
• Begin in the bear crawl position: knees slightly off the ground, back straight, hands under shoulders, and feet under hips.
• Move opposite limbs (right hand, left foot) forward, followed by the left hand, right foot.
• Keep a steady pace to avoid overexertion.
• Focus on engaging your core and maintaining good posture throughout.
Note
Push yourself to complete the full 2-minute duration for a rewarding workout.
"Strength is built one step at a time. Keep crawling towards your goals."
